  "title": "OpenShift System Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage clusters, resource pools, virtual switches, and datastores.</li><li>Utilize vSphere technologies including vCenter, ESXi, vMotion, DRS, and HA.</li><li>Monitor system health dashboards in vCenter; address alerts, failures, and performance degradation.</li><li>Troubleshoot VM resource bottlenecks (CPU, memory, disk, network).</li><li>Provide incident resolution and technical support for Windows system-related issues.</li><li>Conduct performance analysis and tuning for Windows servers.</li><li>Administer Windows Failover Clusters and Always-On Clusters.</li><li>Administer and maintain Hyper-V hosts and virtual machines.</li><li>Configure and manage virtual switches, storage, and failover clustering.</li><li>Monitor performance and availability of Hyper-V environments</li><li>Collaborate with storage, networking, and backup teams for integrated infrastructure support.</li><li>Manage control plane components and worker nodes in OpenShift clusters.</li><li>Monitor node health and resource usage (CPU, memory, disk).</li><li>Analyze logs using OpenShift Cluster logs, Splunk, or external logging services.</li><li>Troubleshoot networking, deployment, and node-level issues in OpenShift.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelors’ Degree in Computer Science or related field.</li><li>At least 6 years’ relevant experience.</li><li>Administer and maintain VMware ESXi hosts and vCenter Server.</li><li>Virtual Infrastructure Management VMware, Hyper-v</li><li>OpenShift Container Platform (OCP)</li><li>Hybrid Cloud AWS / Azure</li></ul>",
